'Consequences' is the debut album by the New York Contemporary Five featuring
saxophonists Archie Shepp and John Tchicai, trumpeter Don Cherry, bassist Don
Moore and drummer J. C. Moses. The album was released on the Fontana label in
1963. [http://www.jazzdisco.org/archie-shepp/discography/ Archie Shepp
discography] accessed 30 July 2009
